It was just plain sweet so the next time I ordered spicy basil chicken with level 3.
It tasted the same.
Sweet.
After that, I craved for some good duck dish so I got their homestyle duck level 5.
The duck was good and had some kick to it.
However, it was still too sweet.
Last night I got kabocha curry with tofu level 5.
I did not want to raise my spice level because I was afraid that I might not be able to eat it.
I now regret getting it with level 5 because it was just as mild as level 3 and was sweet.
I am probably going to return to the restaurant because its close.
But I won't recommend it to anyone who really want authentic thai food.
Their food is too sweet.

